# Instance families & naming

Pick the **family** (workload shape) first, then the size.

## The families

- **General Purpose** (`m7g`, `t3`) — balanced
- **Compute** (`c7g`) — CPU per dollar
- **Memory** (`r7g`, `x2idn`) — RAM per core
- **Storage** (`i4i`) — local NVMe
- **Accelerated** (`p4`, `inf2`) — GPUs / ML chips

## Reading the name — `m7g.xlarge`

`m` family · `7` generation · `g` **Graviton** (ARM; `i` Intel, `a` AMD) · `xlarge` size. **Graviton ≈ 20% cheaper, ~40% better perf/$** — default on ARM.

## T-series — burstable

`t3`/`t4g` run at a **baseline**, earn credits below it, spend to burst above. Great for spiky/idle; **wrong for sustained CPU**.
